      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-13T21:22:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Was this meant to be Null() too?  Or couldn\u0027t most of the others stay NullValue::Make()?  The only reason we have Null() is so that we can take the address of the return value, right?",
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "17a38b21_c75b7763",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T02:42:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, pretty much.  After refactoring, the only method still returning a reference is ObjectValue::operator[].  So we can get rid of Null and fold the static in there.  Done.",
      "parentUuid": "d9dee47f_9ee5c8ac",
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ef3b272a_59d2247e",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-13T21:22:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Reading the new API, I was kind of expecting the const char* constructor to be implemented in terms of the stream constructor, which had now become more fundamental.  Given that we need a length, and we\u0027re going to read the whole thing, and make a copy... doesn\u0027t this constructor seem pointless?  Might be more honest to make any stream-based users do all this buffering for us?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 749,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 755,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4861a51_29445010",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T02:42:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Possibly, I\u0027m just afraid this will become very repetitive in clients, as pretty much all of them would start off with a stream.  Maybe we can add a CStringBuffer helper class to make the buffering operation more transparent?\n\nAnyway, I\u0027m fine with deferring for now, we can deal with this later.\n\nRemoved.",
      "parentUuid": "ef3b272a_59d2247e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 749,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 755,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b3c277cd_e1891bbc",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T14:09:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I figure most people will also have a stream, but I wonder whether they really have an mmap\u0027d piece of data, or something that\u0027s actually streaming in.  If it\u0027s actually streaming in, we probably want to rewrite this to work first-class with streams?  If it\u0027s just a full blob anyway, might as well stick with a full blob passed to the parser.\n\nDoes it simplify things at all to make this take a byte string and a length rather than require a c string null terminator?",
      "parentUuid": "d4861a51_29445010",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 749,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 755,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3014e0b6_e43f62f9",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T14:47:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The current lexer impl is relying heavily on a \\0 terminator (as it folds naturally into the token tests, for free).  If we switch to a length-constrained input, we\u0027ll have to test for EOS on every token read.\n\nSo I\u0027m mostly concerned about perf, but we could give it a shot.  One of the other parser authors estimates ~10% overhead, so maybe not horrible.",
      "parentUuid": "b3c277cd_e1891bbc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 749,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 755,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0a5ad764_756e4e32",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T15:16:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Makes sense.\n\nWhat do you think the cost would be to check for termination only at each \u0027}\u0027, and then up at the beginning return NullValue() if buf[len-1] !\u003d \u0027}\u0027?  Is that sound?",
      "parentUuid": "3014e0b6_e43f62f9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 749,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 755,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "062e7ae6013cbec8bf03811843b4fd279ba3b436",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1a2402bc_1772797a",
        "filename": "modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 755,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-14T15:32:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Awesome idea!  Maybe a bit more involved than that, because trailing white space is also valid, but I think some variation of that should work.  I\u0027ll definitely give it a shot.",
